column1: # The 1860s sheet is shared with nearby Longhills Hall, where the observer A.S.Leslie Melville's wife lived.
# The 1869 readings are for Longhills Hall.
# For a period there were readings in parallel at Branston Hall and Longhills Hall.
# Readings stopped at Branston Hall 1881-1884, but resumed again in 1885, the point at which Longhills Hall readings stop.
